ontologyFramework.OFEventManagement

Interface OFEventInterface

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HasBooleanTrue, IsInClass

    public interface OFEventInterface
extends java.io.Serializable
    This interface is used to define the event procedure. It is called from OFEventDefinition.compute(OFBuildedListInvoker) which calls isCorrectInput(List) first and, if the result is true it calls evaluateEvent(List, OFBuildedListInvoker) and propagate the result to the OFEventAggregation.compute(OFBuildedListInvoker).
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Buoncomapgni Luca

      • isCorrectInput

        boolean isCorrectInput(java.util.List<EventComputedData> inputs)
        sviluppated with safety pourposes it is called to check if the type of parameter in inputs are correct. If this return false the event result of evaluateEvent(List, OFBuildedListInvoker) will be setted to null.
        Parameters:
        inputs - ordered in accord with the ontological definition of the events trhougth the object property "hasTypeEventDefinition
        Returns:
        true if the inputs are corrects. If return else, event computation dennied.
